com.bigdata.ganglia

Class GangliaListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bigdata.ganglia.GangliaListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IGangliaDefaults, Callable<Void>

    public class GangliaListener
extends Object
implements Callable<Void>, IGangliaDefaults
    Class listens in to the Ganglia UDP protocol, decodes received messages, and dispatches them to an IGangliaMessageHandler.

    The decoded messages are reported without any additional translation. The receiver may need to reconcile host names, IGangliaMetadataMessages with those already on hand, and/or reconcile IGangliaMetricMessage with the IGangliaMetadataMessages already on hand. The GangliaListener does NOT perform such operations by design so it maybe used to obtain a faithful transcription of the chatter on the ganglia network.

      • call

        public Void call()
          throws Exception
        Listens for ganglia messages. Each message is decoded as as it is received. Bad packets are dropped. Valid messages are dispatched using a second thread to avoid latency in the thread which is listening to the ganglia protocol.

        Note: This method BLOCKS and does NOT notice an interrupt. This is because JDK 6 does not support multicast NIO. TODO Java 6 does not support non-blocking multicast receive. Write a JDK 7 specific version of class class which uses multicast with non-blocking IO and hence can be interrupted.

        Specified by:
        call in interface Callable<Void>
        Throws:
        Exception
        See Also:
        Multicasting with NIO., MulticastChannel
